Before starting the tasks below:

Install Terraform in your Linux development environment.
Clone starter files here
Tasks:

Task 1.

Create a new SSH keypair in your Linux environment.

Add the public key to the included cloud-init config file

Add packages to cloud-init file to install nginx and nmap packages

See cloud-init docs https://cloudinit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html

Task 2.

Complete the included main.tf file to configure the infrastructure described in the files comments.

Blocks that are incomplete will have a comment specifying what to add. Some blocks are complete

Links to documentation have been provided in block comments.

Task 3.

Connect to the web user created in the cloud-init config using public dns or ip address and the ssh created in task 1.

Demo that you can connect to your instance in class.

Deliverables:

Submit a link to a public Git repository that contains the following:
- "README.md" that contains:
    - Instructions on general set up.
    - Command used to create a new SSH key pair.
    - Commands used to initialize, fmt, plan... configuration.
    - Any other instructions needed to setup configuration
- "main.tf" terraform configuration
- "cloud-config.yaml" cloud-init configuration
